    "content_hash": "d229b9c481704f05",
    "department": "Hardware",
    "description": "About Sesame\n\nSesame believes in a future where computers are lifelike - with the ability to see, hear, and collaborate with us in ways that feel natural and human. With this vision, we're designing a new kind of computer, focused on making voice agents part of our daily lives. Our team brings together founders from Oculus and Ubiquity6, alongside proven leaders from Meta, Google, and Apple, with deep expertise spanning hardware and software. Join us in shaping a future where computers truly come alive.\n\nAbout the Sesame Design Team\n\nWe are a group of individuals who care deeply about our craft. We are obsessive down to fractional millimeters. We have exceptional taste, and live in and are informed by fashion, luxury, and cultural spaces outside of technology. We value radical creativity, and view making and craft as one of the highest forms of human connection. We are passionate about things no one will ever see or know – simply because it’s the right thing to do.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nWe're looking for an Industrial Designer who is passionate about creating luxury eyewear and a supporting accessory portfolio - work that blends refined aesthetics, advanced materials, and thoughtful user experience. This role requires a strong sense of taste and the ability to translate trends, CMF direction, and brand DNA into distinctive, production-ready designs.\n\nYou bring fluency in both soft and hard goods, an eye for the details that most people will never consciously register, and the rigor to see every decision through to production. You will shape products and accessories that express traditional craftsmanship and contemporary design excellence - at the frontier of what personal computing can look and feel like.\n\n\nCONCEPT DEVELOPMENT\n\n - Generate innovative industrial design and CMF concepts that align with our brand’s aesthetic, fashion direction, and user needs.\n\n - Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including engineers, CMF specialists, product managers, and modelers, to explore, develop, and refine concepts.\n\n - Knowledge of materials, manufacturing processes, prototyping and production techniques.\n\n\nDESIGN EXECUTION\n\n - Create detailed sketches, technical drawings to visualize and communicate design intent.\n\n - Develop prototypes and mockups to evaluate proportions, fit, materiality, and aesthetic quality.\n\n - Iterate on designs based on user insights, testing feedback, and internal reviews to optimize comfort, usability, and visual appeal.\n\n\nCOLLABORATION AND COMMUNICATION\n\n - Work closely with engineering, manufacturing partners, and material suppliers to ensure design feasibility and production accuracy.\n\n - Communicate design rationale, specifications, and CMF decisions clearly to internal teams and external vendors.\n\n - Participate in design and prototype reviews, offering constructive feedback to elevate design quality and execution.\n\n\nINDUSTRY TRENDS AND INNOVATION\n\n - Stay informed on global fashion trends, eyewear silhouettes, color directions, and emerging materials.\n\n - Integrate new design approaches, fabrication techniques, and fashion influences into concept development\n   \n\nRequired Qualifications:\n\n - Strong portfolio showcasing both creative and technical design skills.\n\n - 5+ years of professional experience in industrial design, fashion accessories, luxury goods, or closely related consumer product categories; experience in consumer electronics is a strong plus.\n\n - Strong understanding of soft-goods / hard-goods integration, CMF development, and design for manufacturing in the luxury industry.\n\n - High proficiency in 2D design tools (such as Illustrator, Photoshop, or equivalent) for creating detailed drawings, CMF specs, and presentation layouts.\n\n - High proficiency in 3D design tools (Rhinoceros, SolidWorks, Autodesk Alias, or equivalent) for creating detailed, 3D models\n\n - Strong communication skills to present and justify design decisions.\n\n - Exceptional sketching and visualization skills with the ability to communicate design concepts clearly and compellingly.\n\n - Strong aesthetic sensibility, trend awareness, and rigorous and exacting attention to detail.\n\n - Hands-on experience with physical and digital prototyping tools and techniques.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\n - In-depth understanding of materials and manufacturing processes relevant to eyewear, electronics, and luxury accessories.\n\n - Experience applying user-centered design methodologies, human factors, and iterative concept refinement.\n\n - Familiarity with sustainable design practices, responsible material sourcing, and environmentally conscious production methods.\n\n - Strong interest in the luxury fashion market, global design trends, and emerging innovations in eyewear and accessories.\n\n - Experience working with high-end eyewear brands or luxury fashion houses is a significant plus.\n\nSesame is committed to a workplace where everyone feels valued, respected, and empowered. We welcome all qualified applicants, embracing diversity in race, gender, identity, orientation, ability, and more. We provide reasonable accommodations for applicants with disabilities. Contact careers@sesame.com for assistance.\n\nFull-time Employee Benefits: \n\n - 401 (k) max employer match: 3.5% of compensation\n\n - 100% employer-paid health, vision, and dental benefits for you and your dependents\n\n - Unlimited PTO and sick time\n\n - Flexible spending account with employer matching up to $1,650/year (medical FSA)\n\n - Guardian Employee Assistance Program (EAP)\n\n - Opportunity to share in the company's success with competitive stock options\n\nBenefits do not apply to contingent/contract workers.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
